body:
We are looking for a Java architect to join a team that develops the Next Great Platform for In-Car Connectivity!

The project:

Our partner is a global IT player on the German market, mainly involved in automotive industry projects.

The project is the next great platform for In-Car Connectivity!

The automotive industry is undergoing a major change as more and more cars get connected to the Internet. Users get accustomed to storing their content in the cloud and expect to be able to access it from their cars. They also want to access their favorite apps while in a car.

We’re helping them turn the connected vehicle into an intelligent vehicle. Our engineering team works on the next benchmark for in-vehicle connectivity back-end systems for after sales (like live traffic with TomTom) and client services (like auto services).

Responsibilities: 

•	Participates in architectural decisions and creates architectural documentation such as design documents, guidelines, and standards
•	Prototypes and assists development teams
•	Responsible for assisting during production issues on a highly available enterprise product
•	Reviews business requirements and develops architectural specifications and software design
•	Ensures regular communication with team on project progress, issues, and risks, including product and project managers
•	Peer review for junior/mid

Required competencies:

Required Competencies:
Must Have:
•	Design, Technology, OS and tools
•	Java Enterprise Edition 6+ (JPA, JAX-RS, JAX-WS, JMS, JMX, JSF, JAAS, …)
•	REST, SOAP
•	JSON, XML, HTML
•	HTTP(S), SMTP, TCP/IP, IPSEC, etc.
•	Apache HTTP Server
•	Apache Tomcat
•	Windows, Linux
•	Maven
•	Git

Nice to Have:
•	Sun Certified Programmer for the Java Platform (SCJP)
•	Sun Certified Enterprise Architect (SCEA)
•	UML / BPMN
•	Enterprise Application Servers (Jboss, Websphere)
•	RedHat Enterprise Linux (RHEL)
•	MsSQL
•	NoSQL Data Store (Redis, Apache CouchDB, Apache Cassandra; Prototyping possible)
•	SOA/Microservices understanding
•	HTML5, JavaScript, jQuery, AngularJS

We value: 

•	Respect
•	Reliability
•	Striving for excellence






